NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|In Match Points (live bridge) it is more complicated because even if we set 3H, making 3S (+140) is a better score than +50 or +100. In IMPs, on a part score hand, so long as you get some plus, that is fine. But in Match Points, you do better even if you score 10 more points than the opponents. |
PG| ***** 50 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|In Match Points if we can make 3@S or 4 of a minor, we should be there. But in IMPs, scoring +50 or +100 is fine. In IMPs think of it as total score. Another 50 points or so makes little difference. It is the big swings, failing to bid game or slam, that make the difference.|
PG| ***** 51 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|In Match Points, the size of your score is irrelevant. You just have to try and score better than other pairs, even if only by 10 points. In IMPs, if you are plus 100 instead of +110, it makes no difference. On the other hand in Match Points, if you score +110 and all the other pairs are +100, you get a top board.|
